        <td>Number</td>
        <td>Display only products that cost less than the specified value.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="code">category</td>
        <td>String</td>
        <td>Find products that belongs to the specified category path or to a sub category. For example, <code>?category=/shoes</code> matches all producs in categories /shoes, /shoes/running /shoes/classic and other subcategories of "shoes". Accepts also a comma separated list of paths.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="code">collection_id</td>
        <td>Number</td>
        <td>Display only products that belongs to a single collection, given the collection id. To see how to add a product to a collection, please see the <a class="link" href="/documentation/rest-api/collections">collection resource</a>.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>{Attribute}</code></td>
        <td>Mixed</td>
        <td>Filter products by any custom field.</td>
      </tr>
